    "headerDoc": "STEP 956 — Model Theory and Mathematical Logic Open Problems\n  藤本伸樹 2026-04-21\n\n  Five open problems in model theory and logic:\n\n  A. VAUGHT CONJECTURE (1961)\n     For a complete first-order theory T in a countable language:\n     the number of countable models is either ≤ℵ₀, = ℵ₁, or = 2^ℵ₀.\n     (No theory has exactly ℵ₁ countable models if CH fails?)\n     STATUS: OPEN for 60+ years.\n\n  B. SHELAH MAIN GAP THEOREM (1982, PROVED)\n     For a complete first-order theory T:\n     Either T has at most 2^ℵ₀ models in every cardinality (ω-stable,\n     superstable-like), OR T has the maximum number 2^κ"
